.TH domain "" "" "System Administration"
.PC "Set your system's mail domain"
.B /etc/domain
.PP
The file
.B /etc/domain
sets the domain that the \*(CO mail system
uses to create your fully qualified domain name.
Your fully
qualified domain name is created by appending the contents of
.B /etc/domain
to the contents of
.BR /etc/uucpname ,
with an intervening `.'.
Unless you have a registered domain name, the contents of
this file should be
.BR UUCP .
.PP
For information on registering in the United States catch-all domain
.BR .us ,
send mail to:
.DM
	us-domain-request@venera.isi.edu
.DE
.PP
UUNET Communications Services of Falls Church, Virginia, will help
you set up your own domain for a modest fee.
Contact
.B info@uunet.uu.net
for more information; or telephone them at 703-876-5050.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "Administering COHERENT," administe
.Xr "mail," mail
.Xr "paths," paths
.Xr "uucpname" uucpname
